            . I took the prisoner, and found the duplicates on her.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that the prosecutor engaged her as housekeeper, to take the charge of four children, but was too poor to supply them with the common necessaries or pay her wages; that she had pledged the articles to procure his children food.</p>
               <p>JOSHUA FLIGHT re-examined. Q. Have you been in such a state of indigence that you have employed her to pawn your property, or allowed her to do it? A. No - I allowed her money as a housekeeper; she has pawned her own property - I do not owe her any thing; I passed my word at a tally-shop, and a man has come to me for it.</p>
               <p>Four witnesses gave the prisoner a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 49.</p>
